<TEXT>
a former berks county district attorney and 
a onetime candidate for mayor in reading were indicted thursday on 
federal charges of supplying chemicals to three readingarea drug 
operations 
j michael morrissey who served as berks county district 
attorney from 197680 and joseph pastore are charged with 
conspiracy to manufacture methamphetamine and phenyl2propanone 
or p2p a key ingredient in methamphetamine 
the indictment says morrissey a practicing attorney and 
pastore delivered chemicals laboratory equipment and recipes for 
methamphetamine or p2p to drug manufacturers from june 1985 to 
february 1986 
three others named in the indictment were not charged 
pastores lawyer emmanuel h dimitriu refused to comment on 
the indictment morrisseys lawyer william bernhart did not 
return telephone calls for comment 
mary vaira of the federal drug enforcement administration 
described morrissey as a broker 
according to the indictment in june 1985 morrissey delivered 
phenyl acetic acid an ingredient of p2p to arthur auchenbach who 
was charged separately thursday with manufacturing p2p 
pastore and two others not charged delivered about 200 pounds of 
phenyl acetic acid in december 1985 to a farm in bethel township 
according to the indictment pastore also provided drug 
manufacturers with the telephone numbers of individuals supplying 
p2p to morrissey the indictment says 
the indictment also charges morrissey 51 of myerstown with one 
count of aiding and abetting the manufacture of p2p pastore also 
is charged with distributing one quart of p2p 
if convicted on all counts morrissey faces a maximum penalty of 
60 years imprisonment and a fine of 500000 pastore 65 of west 
reading faces a maximum penalty of 30 years and a 250000 fine 
and auchenbach faces a maximum penalty of 20 years and a 1 million 
fine 
marrissey and pastore were scheduled for arraignment friday in 
philadelphia before magistrate william f hall said assistant us 
attorney lee j dobkin 
</TEXT>
