nearly three of every four rural households 
pay more for housing than the government considers affordable with 
about a quarter of all rural residents living in substandard 
dwellings says a new report 
to many americans the lowincome housing crisis is primarily 
an urban problem calling up visions of homeless men and women 
sleeping on steam grates and of families in city welfare hotels 
said robert greenstein director of the center on budget and policy 
priorities 
yet in rural america too there is a crisis in housing for 
