carolina households still use outhouses 
the report found that 42 percent of rural poor households spent 
at least half of their income on housing in 1985 the most recent 
year for which data is available it said 26 percent spent 70 
percent or more for housing 
the department of housing and urban development has standards 
that say housing is not considered affordable unless it is 30 
percent or less of a familys income 
