irancontra defendant john poindexter says 
former president reagan is trying to avoid political criticism in 
attempting to quash a subpoena for his diaries 
poindexters lawyers challenged both reagan and president bush 
to invoke executive privilege in their attempts to quash defense 
subpoenas for the former presidents diaries and papers 
reagan and the justice department moved to quash the subpoenas 
but on legal grounds other than executive privilege 
obviously their legal position is carefully calculated to 
avoid subjecting them to the political consequences of their 
invoking the privilege including the consequent public perception 
that mr reagan and mr bush are still attempting to hide the true 
facts regarding their involvement in the socalled irancontra 
affair poindexters lawyers said in a court filing 
