what i take to be an expression of concern about the nature of the 
compelled sentencing process that congress has imposed upon the 
courts 
the new federal drug law effective last november requires 
prison sentences without parole for certain types of drug crimes 
decisions that were formerly left up to the sentencing judge 
a first offender who possessed over 50 grams of crack cocaine 
for sale for example must serve at least 10 years without parole 
with a prior felony drug conviction the minimum sentence is 20 
years and with two prior drug felonies the mandatory sentence is 
life without the possibility of parole 
