the bay fronting some of the worlds mostvisited beaches has 
provided background scenery to hollywood productions including the 
beach blanket movies gidget tv series and the film 
tequila sunrise 
it touches about 40 miles of wide whitesand beach from the 
palos verdes peninsula in the south to malibu in the north 
the agreement between the regional water quality control board 
and the city of los angeles lists 22 measures the city must pursue 
with costs estimated to surpass 100 million officials said 
thursday 
this is the way controversies between two government agencies 
should be handled mayor tom bradley said instead of fighting 
it out in the courts we solved it at the bargaining table 
the city agreed to take steps to prevent raw sewage spills at a 
treatment plant reduce pollutants washing out to sea from storm 
drains and improve sewage treatment 
a rash of sewage spills in 1987 prompted county health officials 
to close miles of beach angering surfers scuba divers and 
environmentalists 
the city also pledged to create new water reclamation and 
conservation programs and stage a museum exhibit to heighten public 
awareness on bay pollution 
the pact was approved by the city council in a closeddoor 
meeting tuesday and announced on thursday 
virtually all costs will be borne by the citys sewage surcharge 
tax imposed on homeowners and commercial landlords city officials 
said 
state attorney general john k van de kamp filed the suit in 
1987 seeking penalties of up to 20 a gallon for two major spills 
that dumped more than 54 million gallons of raw sewage into the 
bay 
</TEXT>
