sammy lerner the hollywood songwriter whose 
lyrics im strong to the finich cause i eats me spinach 
created a loyal following for popeye the sailor man has died of 
cancer he was 86 
lerner died wednesday at a los angeles nursing home said a 
spokeswoman for the american society of composers authors and 
publishers 
the serious songwriter said he was horrified by the 1932 theme 
im popeye the sailor man which he composed in less than two 
hours for cartoonist dave fleischer 
when i saw that first cartoon i wanted to crawl in a 
corner lerner said in a 1977 interview just do me a favor 
i said dont put my name on the screen 
lerner was as adept at nonsense cartoon lyrics as he was with 
the romantic and breezy standards of tin pan alley 
his work in the 1930s and 1940s included is it true what they 
say about dixie a song immortalized by al jolson and english 
lyrics to falling in love again marlene dietrichs song in the 
film the blue angel 
lerner also wrote the theme for betty boop and a number of 
bouncing ball musical cartoon songs 
born in saveni romania in 1903 lerner emigrated with his 
family to detroit where he attended wayne state university 
he began writing songs for vaudeville acts and lyrics for the 
ziegfeld follies stage shows in new york soon he was composing 
lyrics for cartoons in hollywood and songs for film musicals 
including blondie meets the boss the lady vanishes and 
lady from cheyenne 
he collaborated with such popular composers as hoagy carmichael 
richard whiting gerald marks irving caesar and burton lane 
lerner is survived by his wife of 53 years dorothy 
