bomb either started or passed through the frankfurt airport 
where the flight originated west german police maintain there is 
not enough evidence to prove that 
fraser and esson were asked about mohammad abu talb a member of 
another radical palestinian group who is charged in sweden with 
four bombings in northern europe he was identified in a swedish 
court as a suspect in the lockerbie bombing and police seized 
clothing from his home reportedly to compare with shreds of 
clothing found in the wreckage 
i have at present no intention to seek the extradition of abu 
talb fraser said 
esson said he is certainly an individual in whom we have an 
interest he added that investigators wanted to talk with many 
people but he refused to identify them further 
fraser asked about the contents of the baggage that contained 
