the national transportation safety board said 
today it will conduct a hearing focusing on boeing 737 rudder trim 
design and cockpit performance in the crash of a usair jetliner at 
new yorks laguardia airport 
the fourday hearing is to begin feb 13 at the penta hotel in 
new york said spokesman ted lopatkiewicz 
the sept 20 accident in which the aircraft skidded off the end 
of the runway into new yorks east river after pilots aborted its 
takeoff killed two passengers the plane lodged on a landing pier 
and broke into pieces 
board chairman james kolstad who will conduct the hearing said 
he expects about 16 witnesses to testify on cockpit crew training 
and coordination design and operation of the rudder trim system 
and other issues 
as tragic as this accident was it could have been much 
worse kolstad said we have mechanical and human performance 
issues to resolve in the course of this investigation and the 
hearing will provide us with valuable information on both issues 
the board did not announce who the witnesses would be but 
surviving crew members often testify at such hearings we may not 
know until just before the hearing whether they will appear said 
lopatkiewicz 
investigators said the planes tail rudder used in steering the 
airliner was misaligned despite evidence that the crew made all 
the proper checks the pilot reported the plane was drifting to the 
left before he aborted the takeoff this focused attention on the 
trim system that holds the rudder steady during takeoff 
the federal aviation administration suspended the pilots 
licenses of capt michael w martin and copilot constantine 
kleissas after the crash for their failure to appear immediately 
for drug tests and questioning by investigators 
the safety boards new york hearing will include a panel of 
senior ntsb staff members and a technical panel of investigators 
as well as representatives of the faa the boeing co and the air 
line pilots association 
the board which is an independent federal agency has no 
rulemaking or enforcement powers its findings of probable cause 
and recommendations will be included in a report to be adopted at a 
public meeting several months after the hearing although it can 
issue urgent recommendations at any time 
