britains annual inflation rate rose to 77 
percent in november from 73 percent in october pushed up by 
higher mortgage rates the government said friday 
the underlying inflation rate excluding mortgage payments was 
unchanged at 61 percent the central statistical office said 
the financial markets had little reaction to the latest 
inflation rate which was better than had been expected 
