chancellor of the exchequer john major recently announced that more 
expensive home loans would push the retail price index up 
the government has pushed up interest rates sharply to fight 
inflation but the policy has the ironic effect of inflating the 
inflation rate 
major and prime minister margaret thatcher have said repeatedly 
that fighting inflation is their no 1 economic priority and that 
interest rates will stay high as long as is necessary 
