pen selecting a nib can take hours nib widths vary to produce 
fine to very broad scripts and the shape of ones penmanship 
depends on the pressure exterted on the nib and the angle it is 
held against the paper 
over time the nib conforms to an individual user and for that 
reason one should never lend it wendell said 
but despite a luxury pens ability to elegantly paint words how 
they write often is less important than how they look parkers 
marketing planner greg watts said one businesswoman told him i 
dont use this pen to write with i wear it 
