lower than was feared earlier this year 
the index dipped 01 percent last month following a 04 percent 
gain in october and a 09 percent spurt in september it declined 
05 percent in july and 04 percent in august 
the rollercoaster ride averages out to an annualized inflation 
rate of about 1 percent from june through november a marked 
contrast to the 9 percentplus rate for the first five months of 
the year 
if ever there was an example of inflation coming in like a 
lion and going out like a lamb it was this year said economist 
david jones of aubrey g lanston amp co a government securities 
dealer in new york that has to be good news for everyone 
particularly the consumer 
energy prices declined 33 percent last month the sharpest fall 
since august a 77 percent drop in gasoline prices more than 
compensated for a 01 percent rise in natural gas costs and a 07 
percent hike in heating oil prices 
analysts credit the taming of inflation to the federal reserves 
tight money policy pursued through this spring as evidence they 
cited a separate report by the fed on industrial production in 
november 
the operating rate at the nations factories mines and 
utilities eased 01 percentage point to 827 percent well below 
the 10year high of 843 percent at the start of the year the 
central bank said 
areas that were tight a year ago like chemicals paper and 
metals all have excess capacity when you have excess capacity you 
see price concessions said economist donald ratajczak of georgia 
state university 
since the summer the fed has reversed course on monetary 
policy hoping to avoid a recession by permitting interest rates to 
fall 
the latest price report gives the fed leeway to cut rates 
another notch as early as next week when monetary policy makers 
gather for the last of their eight annual meetings economists said 
a disappointing trade report for october adds impetus to the 
push according to the commerce department the merchandise trade 
gap soared 198 percent to 102 billion the highest level in 10 
months 
a drop in us interest rates could help the deficit by 
depressing the dollars value stimulating exports and discouraging 
imports 
the wholesale price report showed food costs rising a 
substantial 08 percent in november following a 14 percent jump 
in october the biggest in 22 months however they had declined 
overall from april through september 
pork prices jumped 71 percent following a 95 percent rise in 
october prices for turkeys and eggs also rose and dairy prices 
were up 33 percent the fifth consecutive increase exceeding 1 
percent 
because of the drought of 88 we slaughtered a lot of milk 
cows and were starting to see a milk shortage as a result 
ratajczak said its going to take a year to reverse that 
the increases were partly offset by a 151 percent drop in 
vegetable costs rebounding from an 189 percent rise a month 
earlier and a 65 percent decline in fresh fruit prices prices 
for fish chicken coffee and rice also fell 
the price of goods excluding the volatile food and energy 
categories a measure many analysts consider a better gauge of 
underlying inflationary pressures in the economy rose a modest 
02 percent last month following a 01 percent gain in october 
increases for a variety of goods were partly offset by a 48 
percent decline for soaps and detergents and a 03 percent decrease 
in the passenger car index which had fallen 14 percent in october 
before adjusting for normal seasonal variations the wholesale 
