minivans from gm and mazda motor corp and those already in 
showrooms from ford and a halfdozen or so japanese companies 
chrysler expects to introduce a new version of its dodge caravan 
and plymouth voyager next fall for the 1991 model year 
production at chryslers minivan plants in windsor ontario and 
st louis mo will be shut down in the third week of june and the 
third week of july respectively to change equipment for the new 
models 
the changeovers will take about four weeks bidwell said 
analysts have speculated that automakers faced with swelling 
inventories and waning demand may cut their supplies of unsold 
cars by curtailing production during the first quarter of 1990 
