a 09 percent rise in september 
analysts said the producerprice index figure was better than 
expected while the trade deficit growth was worse the reports 
negated each other in impact on the credit markets 
the general gist of all the evidence weve had over the entire 
week is that we have a pretty sluggish situation in the conomy 
said jean buckley an economist at bankamerica capital markets 
group in san francisco 
but there was nothing either great or harmful to get things 
moving she said the market is very quiet there arent that 
many positions in the street now 
bondholders have welcomed recent news of a slowing economy 
because it implies less demand for goods and services easing the 
risk of inflation which erodes the value of bonds 
slower growth also encourages the federal reserve to take steps 
that would lower interest rates to stimulate the economy lower 
rates make fixedincome investments such as bonds more valuable 
economists said they believe the fed could ease interest rates 
next week 
in the secondary market for treasury securities prices of 
shortterm issues were down 132 point to 116 point 
intermediateterm maturities were 116 point to 332 point lower 
and longterm issues were unchanged to down 132 point according 
to figures provided by telerate inc a financial information 
service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer was down 034 at 119565 
yields on threemonth treasury bills rose to 788 percent as the 
discount gained 2 basis points to 764 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills rose to 778 percent while the discount rose 1 basis point to 
740 percent yields on oneyear bills issued at auction thursday 
were at 763 percent with the discount off 1 basis points to 713 
percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks was quoted at 8 percent down from 8716 percent late 
thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds closed at 93 2332 up 132 point the 
average yield to maturity was unchanged at 724 percent 
