the us merchandise trade deficit surged to 
102 billion in october the worst imbalance in 10 months as a 
record level of imports swamped a small rise in exports the 
commerce department said 
the october deficit was a sharp 198 percent higher than the 
september imbalance of 851 billion reflecting a higher foreign 
oil bill and big increases in imports of food and industrial 
supplies the government said friday 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a sharp drop in gasoline costs helped push 
wholesale prices down in november for the third time in five 
months the government reported 
the annual rate of inflation as measured by the labor 
departments producer price index released friday was 46 percent 
for the first 11 months of the year up from 4 percent for all of 
1988 but much lower than was feared earlier this year 
the index dipped 01 percent last month following a 04 percent 
gain in october and a 09 percent spurt in september it declined 
05 percent in july and 04 percent in august 
</TEXT>
