<TEXT>
the brokerage firm prudentialbache securities 
inc has agreed to pay a 100000 fine and be censured for stock 
pricing violations following the 1987 market crash the national 
association of securities dealers said friday 
in addition prudentialbache made adjustments of 
23590150 in the prices customers paid in connection with the 
questioned transactions the association said in a statement 
in settling the matter prudentialbache neither admitted nor 
denied the allegations the statement said 
the associations market surveillance committee said 
prudentialbache received sell orders involving 20 securities for 
which it was the market maker on oct 19 1987 but failed to 
complete the sales while the market was open 
it said the firm subsequently bought the securities from the 
customers at prices that were at least 8 percent below the lowest 
reported price of the day 
as a result the committee said the 186 customer accounts 
placing the sell orders received 23590150 less than what they 
would have received had the orders been executed at the lowest 
price of the day 
the allegations involve activities on black monday when the dow 
jones industrial average plunged 508 points in its biggest oneday 
loss ever 
prudentialbache was unable to execute the trades until after 
the close of the market because of the extraordinary market 
conditions 
but the association said that the firm had access before it made 
the deals to information that indicated the intraday trading range 
for these securities 
the national association of securities dealers is a 
selfregulatory organization for the overthecounter markets its 
surveillance committee is responsible for maintaining the integrity 
of those markets 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

